    cellular: "OTs are primary providers of upper extremity rehabilitation following injury, surgery, or neurological conditions. Assessment includes range of motion (goniometry), strength (manual muscle testing, dynamometry), sensation, coordination, and functional use. Common conditions: fractures, tendon repairs, nerve injuries, repetitive strain injuries, and post-surgical rehabilitation. Protocols follow tissue healing timelines: inflammatory phase (0-5 days), fibroplasia (5-21 days), and remodeling (21 days-2 years). Therapeutic exercises progress from passive to active-assisted to active to resistive. Functional activities integrate ROM, strength, and coordination demands. Edema management: elevation, retrograde massage, compression wrapping, and active motion.",
