    cellular: "Hand therapy is a specialized area of OT treating upper extremity conditions. Common diagnoses: carpal tunnel syndrome, trigger finger, de Quervain's tenosynovitis, dupuytren's contracture, tendon repairs (flexor and extensor), fractures, and nerve injuries. Flexor tendon repair protocols have evolved from immobilization to early active motion programs. Extensor tendon zones determine rehabilitation approach. Nerve injuries follow predictable recovery patterns based on Seddon classification: neurapraxia (temporary, full recovery), axonotmesis (axon damage, slow recovery), and neurotmesis (complete disruption, surgical repair needed). Sensory reeducation follows nerve recovery. Desensitization addresses hypersensitivity.",
