    cellular: "Orthotic fabrication is a core OT skill. Purposes include immobilization (protecting healing structures), mobilization (applying forces to increase ROM), restriction (limiting motion in one plane while allowing others), and function (enabling hand function). Common splints: resting hand splint, wrist cock-up splint, thumb spica, dynamic extension splint, and anti-claw splint. Fabrication principles: proper anatomical landmarks, arches of the hand maintained, appropriate thermoplastic material selection, smooth edges, adequate strapping, and patient education on wear schedule. Splint monitoring includes skin checks, fit reassessment, and modification as condition changes. Patient compliance requires understanding purpose and comfortable fit.",
