    cellular: "OTs address feeding (getting food to the mouth) and may contribute to swallowing assessment and intervention in some settings. Feeding assessment evaluates positioning, utensil use, oral motor skills, sensory responses to food, and self-feeding skills. Common interventions: positioning for safe swallowing (upright, chin tuck), adaptive utensils (built-up handles, weighted utensils, scoop dish), food texture modification, sensory-based feeding approaches for children with food selectivity, and oral motor exercises. Dysphagia management is typically led by speech-language pathology, with OT addressing the feeding and positioning components. Tube feeding management includes transition-to-oral-feeding programs.",
